A) INLINE CSS

File: inline.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Online Learning Portal - Inline CSS</title>
</head>

<body>

<h1 style="color: teal; text-align: center;">
    ONLINE LEARNING PORTAL
</h1>

<p style="font-size:18px; color: darkgreen;">
Welcome to the online learning portal. This content is styled using Inline CSS.
</p>

<button style="background: orange; padding: 10px; border: none; color:white;">
Explore Courses
</button>

</body>
</html>

B) INTERNAL CSS
File: internal.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Online Learning Portal - Internal CSS</title>

<style>
body {
    font-family: Arial;
    background-color: #eef6ff;
}

h1 {
    text-align: center;
    color: navy;
}

p {
    font-size: 18px;
    margin: 20px;
    color: #333;
}

button {
    background-color: teal;
    color: white;
    padding: 10px 15px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 6px;
}
</style>

</head>

<body>

<h1>Online Learning Portal</h1>
<p>This webpage uses Internal CSS for styling course information.</p>
<button>View Dashboard</button>

</body>
</html>

 C) EXTERNAL CSS
File 1: external.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Online Learning Portal - External CSS</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>

<body>

<h1>Online Learning Portal</h1>
<p>This page is styled using an External CSS file.</p>
<button>Login</button>

</body>
</html>
File 2: style.css
body {
    font-family: Verdana;
    background-color: #e3f2fd;
}

h1 {
    text-align: center;
    color: purple;
    margin-top: 30px;
}

p {
    font-size: 18px;
    margin: 20px;
    color: #444;
}

button {
    background-color: #ff4081;
    color: white;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 6px;
}
